/table>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#94EBFF","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">This protocol explains how to design and clone the guide RNA target sequence into a L1 plasmid ready to accept the gRNA by cloning with BbsI. L1 plasmids are L1_lacZgRNA-Ck2 and L1_lacZgRNA-Ck3.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>If one gRNA target sequence is cloned into the Ck2 plasmid and another one into Ck3 one, the two L1_gRNA transcription units can be combined with an antibiotic resistance transcription unit and a MpEF1\u03b1:Cas9 transcription unit via <\/span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/view\/loop-l2-even-level-sapi-type-iis-cloning-into-pcs-92fh8bn\" style = \"text-decoration:underline;color:blue;cursor:pointer;\"><span style = \":;\">L2 SapI Loop assembly.<\/span><\/a><span> This allows for dual gRNA editing.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1583219824}